WEBVTT

00:00.334 --> 00:02.634
<i>Previously on "major crimes"...</i>

00:02.636 --> 00:04.737
Heroin. Found underneath
the baby's car seat.

00:04.739 --> 00:06.572
Sykes: 3-year-old boy
went to the hospital -- d.O.A.

00:06.574 --> 00:08.574
Look, this is cannot be true!
Stop lying to me!

00:08.576 --> 00:11.176
Sir, we would not lie to you
about the death of your child!

00:11.178 --> 00:12.578
Sykes: Our victims were shot
with the same gun

00:12.580 --> 00:14.380
that killed officer Reese
and d.D.A. Gray?

00:14.382 --> 00:17.416
We found the murder weapon
in the altar of your church.

00:17.418 --> 00:19.485
Every now and then I find
something to celebrate.

00:19.487 --> 00:20.953
Like finally having
a chance

00:20.955 --> 00:22.254
to leave the uzi
where we'd find it?

00:22.256 --> 00:24.289
Taylor: Hickman perjured himself
on the stand.

00:24.291 --> 00:27.292
He lost us the murder case
of an L.A. cop.

00:27.294 --> 00:28.727
Rusty:
How stupid could he be?

00:28.729 --> 00:31.363
Putting his mask on after
he started the robbery.

00:31.365 --> 00:32.798
Cooper: Classic signs
of a struggle.

00:32.800 --> 00:33.999
And my mom's gone.

00:34.001 --> 00:35.801
L.A.P.D.!

00:35.803 --> 00:37.202
-Gary!
-Gary, stop!

00:37.204 --> 00:38.470
Hey, hey, hey!

00:38.472 --> 00:40.506
Make a deal
where you give up Gary.

00:40.508 --> 00:42.641
He will kill you.
Do you understand?

00:42.643 --> 00:44.076
I know the guy
Emile's living with.

00:44.078 --> 00:45.144
Runs a chop shop.

00:45.146 --> 00:46.812
Buddha, I presume.

00:46.814 --> 00:48.113
And do you have any idea

00:48.115 --> 00:49.448
where his heroin
might have come from?

00:49.450 --> 00:51.050
No, I don't know anything
about any heroin.

00:51.052 --> 00:52.851
-Drop your gun!
-No.

00:52.853 --> 00:54.853
Not now.
He's confessing.

00:54.855 --> 00:56.555
Mark hickman, you have the right
to remain silent.

00:56.557 --> 00:58.057
Anything you say
can and will

00:58.059 --> 00:59.491
be used against you
in a court of law.

01:01.228 --> 01:03.962
Flynn:
Are you sick, ill, or injured?

01:03.964 --> 01:05.164
No.

01:05.166 --> 01:07.800
Do you have any
suicidal tendencies?

01:07.802 --> 01:12.204
When I think I could have
ended up like you.

01:13.307 --> 01:15.441
Put your arm
through the window.

01:15.443 --> 01:17.776
Right arm.

01:19.280 --> 01:21.346
Are you taking
any medications?

01:21.348 --> 01:23.115
Pills
for high blood pressure.

01:23.117 --> 01:25.584
I'm shocked.
Are you an alcoholic?

01:25.586 --> 01:28.253
Nope.

01:28.255 --> 01:29.721
How many drinks do you have
a day?

01:31.826 --> 01:33.325
Not enough.

01:33.327 --> 01:34.226
Okay.

01:34.228 --> 01:35.527
I'll alert medical
to make sure

01:35.529 --> 01:36.995
you don't go through
any withdrawals

01:36.997 --> 01:38.864
during your stay with us.

01:38.866 --> 01:40.165
Empty your pockets,

01:40.167 --> 01:42.634
take your laces
from your shoes,

01:42.636 --> 01:44.369
remove your belt,

01:44.371 --> 01:46.171
and pass them all
through the window.

01:46.173 --> 01:47.606
[ Keys jingle ]
My belt?

01:47.608 --> 01:49.308
Really?

01:49.310 --> 01:51.143
I told you
I'm not suicidal.

01:51.145 --> 01:54.313
Your word's no good here
anymore.

01:55.816 --> 01:58.584
[ Coins clatter ]

02:00.054 --> 02:01.620
Let's go.

02:06.127 --> 02:07.860
[ Knock on door, door buzzes ]

02:12.233 --> 02:13.765
He's former l.A.P.D.,

02:13.767 --> 02:15.467
so make sure
we put a keep-away on him

02:15.469 --> 02:17.336
when we send him to county.

02:17.338 --> 02:20.739
Put your feet on the steps
marked out on the ground.

02:23.811 --> 02:25.377
Look up.

02:29.950 --> 02:32.217
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

02:43.364 --> 02:44.863
I'm not talking to her.

02:44.865 --> 02:47.232
Then I'll take you to county.
That what you want?

02:47.234 --> 02:48.800
What about
the girl scout?

02:48.802 --> 02:52.638
Detective Sykes is busy.

02:52.640 --> 02:54.072
Here.

02:54.074 --> 02:56.408
[ Police radio chatter ]

03:00.147 --> 03:02.781
Attempted murder?
Bullshit.

03:02.783 --> 03:05.083
I just wanted to
have a little man-to-man

03:05.085 --> 03:06.518
with the good reverend.
That's all.

03:06.520 --> 03:08.253
You brought a gun
into his church.

03:08.255 --> 03:09.555
I have a permit to carry.

03:09.557 --> 03:12.624
You won't
after I write my report.

03:12.626 --> 03:15.360
Doesn't this feel
a little too familiar, mark?

03:15.362 --> 03:17.896
You sitting across the table
from me

03:17.898 --> 03:20.432
trying to justify
why you broke the law?

03:20.434 --> 03:25.304
Earlier tonight, I got
reverend copkiller
to confess, okay?

03:25.306 --> 03:26.705
He confessed
to shooting Reese.

03:26.707 --> 03:28.707
I recorded
the whole damn thing.

03:28.709 --> 03:30.776
You held a gun to his head.
It wasn't a confession.

03:30.778 --> 03:34.012
Not to mention that the guy
cannot be tried again

03:34.014 --> 03:35.380
for Reese's murder.

03:35.382 --> 03:37.449
Well, what about
the murder of Rachel gray

03:37.451 --> 03:39.017
and the murder of
Eric Dunn?

03:39.019 --> 03:41.620
Reverend copkiller
is absolved of those shootings

03:41.622 --> 03:43.422
because he --
he carries a Bible?

03:43.424 --> 03:44.856
The only reason he's free

03:44.858 --> 03:47.125
is because you committed perjury
on the stand.

03:47.127 --> 03:48.894
Listen, pollyanna,

03:48.896 --> 03:52.397
if you got rid of every cop
on the l.A.P.D.

03:52.399 --> 03:54.099
Who committed perjury,

03:54.101 --> 03:58.136
there'd be no one left here
but you and your I.A. Friends.

03:58.138 --> 04:01.240
What makes me the bad guy

04:01.242 --> 04:03.642
is that my partner
wouldn't back me up.

04:03.644 --> 04:06.311
<i> -"Lieutenant Michael tao."</i>
-See? It's my fault.

04:06.313 --> 04:09.047
<i> "Did you also</i>
<i> overhear Daniel price,</i>

04:09.049 --> 04:11.383
a.K.A.
Revered copkiller,

04:11.385 --> 04:13.619
confess to the murder of
officer Reese?"

04:13.621 --> 04:16.788
If Mike
had just said yes...

04:16.790 --> 04:21.059
Why did you not
disclose your affair

04:21.061 --> 04:25.564
with d.D.A. Rachel gray
after she was murdered?

04:25.566 --> 04:27.099
How does it
figure into anything?

04:27.101 --> 04:30.402
Because Rachel gray
broke up with your sorry ass

04:30.404 --> 04:31.837
right before the trial.

04:31.839 --> 04:32.804
So?

04:32.806 --> 04:34.373
So you were
in love with her,

04:34.375 --> 04:37.743
and she left you,
and she ended up dead.

04:37.745 --> 04:41.313
You thought of Rachel gray
as the one.

04:41.315 --> 04:44.583
She thought of you
as just one more.

04:44.585 --> 04:47.286
And if you did
kill Rachel and Eric,

04:47.288 --> 04:50.656
that would explain why the
l.A.P.D. Never found the uzi.

04:50.658 --> 04:53.792
Because the third person
in the car came back for it.

04:53.794 --> 04:57.095
Or Emile knew that you'd found
it and where you'd put it.

04:57.097 --> 04:59.765
And that's the reason you met
him when he came out of prison,

04:59.767 --> 05:03.535
and you told him to
keep his mouth shut or else.

05:03.537 --> 05:06.305
And that explains
the "why now" of it all

05:06.307 --> 05:08.640
for your simple minds,
huh?

05:08.642 --> 05:10.842
Shaky Emile
returns to the world

05:10.844 --> 05:13.745
and makes for
a great alternative suspect.

05:13.747 --> 05:16.581
<i> And I shoot this tamika girl</i>
<i> and her baby</i>

05:16.583 --> 05:19.051
<i> because, I don't know,</i>
<i> I'm just that depraved.</i>

05:19.053 --> 05:21.520
<i> Hoping that it will look like</i>
<i> Emile's revenge,</i>

05:21.522 --> 05:24.856
<i> I plant the gun in</i>
<i> reverend copkiller's church.</i>

05:24.858 --> 05:27.292
And this phone.

05:27.294 --> 05:29.528
You planted it, too.

05:29.530 --> 05:32.297
And that's important why?

05:32.299 --> 05:35.400
Because someone used it
to call both tamika and Emile

05:35.402 --> 05:36.835
right before
they were murdered.

05:36.837 --> 05:39.404
A-and did you find
my fingerprints on it?

05:39.406 --> 05:41.006
Of course not.
It was wiped.

05:41.008 --> 05:45.177
Like the uzi and the syringe
we found next Emile's body.

05:45.179 --> 05:46.945
And also like them,

05:46.947 --> 05:51.350
this phone had residue of
cornstarch all over it.

05:51.352 --> 05:53.919
And -- and where did I
plant this phone?

05:53.921 --> 05:55.320
Peter Goldman's car.

05:55.322 --> 05:58.123
Right,
reverend copkiller's lawyer.

05:58.125 --> 06:01.693
Obviously, Daniel price left
this phone in Goldman's car.

06:01.695 --> 06:04.730
Price must cut his dope
with cornstarch.

06:04.732 --> 06:07.232
It's probably all over
his so-called church.

06:07.234 --> 06:09.201
Check the soles
of your shoes.

06:09.203 --> 06:11.269
-You'll see.
-Odd, though.

06:11.271 --> 06:14.906
Once again, we find evidence
linking price to a murder,

06:14.908 --> 06:17.843
then,
by complete coincidence,

06:17.845 --> 06:20.212
you are
just a few feet away.

06:20.214 --> 06:23.815
Was I trying to frame the guy
today or kill him?

06:23.817 --> 06:25.984
I-I think you should
make a choice there.

06:27.121 --> 06:30.522
<i> Look, I-I know this might</i>
<i> hurt your tiny heads,</i>

06:30.524 --> 06:32.724
<i> but try thinking</i>
<i> for a minute.</i>

06:32.726 --> 06:35.694
<i> If I had located the uzi</i>
<i> years ago,</i>

06:35.696 --> 06:39.264
<i> Daniel price would have never</i>
<i> gotten away with murder.</i>

06:39.266 --> 06:40.899
He has a point.

06:40.901 --> 06:43.268
The gun would have
corroborated Emile's statement

06:43.270 --> 06:45.670
and the case
would have been made.
<i> And one more thing --</i>
<i> Rachel...</i>

06:45.672 --> 06:48.440
Rachel left me
because I couldn't find the gun.

06:48.442 --> 06:50.475
Thought I'd let her down.

06:50.477 --> 06:52.377
Thought I'd failed her.

06:52.379 --> 06:55.113
And I...

06:55.115 --> 06:56.615
[ Grunts ]

06:57.718 --> 07:01.119
...I would have never
killed her,

07:01.121 --> 07:04.256
because I know she would have
come back to me...

07:04.258 --> 07:06.057
If she had lived.

07:06.059 --> 07:08.126
I know she would have.

07:09.129 --> 07:12.431
I...I know it.

07:15.736 --> 07:17.402
Write down where you were

07:17.404 --> 07:20.472
when d.D.A. Rachel gray
and Eric Dunn were shot to death

07:20.474 --> 07:22.140
and where you were
when tamika Weaver

07:22.142 --> 07:24.576
and her young son
were shot to death

07:24.578 --> 07:27.379
and where you were
when Emile overdosed.

07:27.381 --> 07:28.580
[ Sighs ]

07:28.582 --> 07:30.916
And we'll run it down.

07:35.422 --> 07:39.090
This isn't
getting us anywhere.

07:40.027 --> 07:42.861
Steph: Shame we had to release
Peter Goldman.

07:42.863 --> 07:46.164
He knows something about
the reverend's drug trade.

07:46.166 --> 07:47.833
Jon Barnes come home yet?

07:47.835 --> 07:49.768
I'm thinking
his house is blown.

07:49.770 --> 07:51.269
He's got to know
we're watching it.

07:51.271 --> 07:55.173
Hey, uh, so what you said
the other night about...

07:55.175 --> 07:57.309
Holding people accountable...

07:57.311 --> 08:00.111
-Yeah?
-Yeah, so, uh...

08:00.113 --> 08:03.348
I made an appointment
with that doctor.

08:03.350 --> 08:04.716
You know,
the one who told my wife

08:04.718 --> 08:07.118
that it was okay
to drop her seizure meds.

08:07.120 --> 08:11.289
Gonna see him the day
after tomorrow in the morning.

08:11.291 --> 08:13.558
Wow, julio, that --

08:13.560 --> 08:16.428
you think you can do that
without shooting him?

08:16.430 --> 08:17.729
That's the number-one reason

08:17.731 --> 08:19.931
why I waited so long
before talking to him.

08:19.933 --> 08:22.834
[ Chuckles ] Want to discuss
some of the dumb things

08:22.836 --> 08:24.269
he might say to you first?

08:24.271 --> 08:26.605
I'm about to wrap this up
'cause I have nothing to do.

08:26.607 --> 08:30.675
Uh, I'm a little busy right now,
Steph.

08:30.677 --> 08:33.645
What about dinner tomorrow
if we get a break?

08:33.647 --> 08:35.580
Oh, yeah.
Dinner sounds great. Sure.

08:35.582 --> 08:37.415
Yeah, I-I'll be over there
in the morning.

08:37.417 --> 08:38.416
We can figure that out.

08:38.418 --> 08:40.385
Julio?

08:40.387 --> 08:42.320
Okay,
then we'll see you then.

08:42.322 --> 08:43.989
Thank you.

08:44.892 --> 08:46.925
Jon Barnes
show his face anywhere?

08:46.927 --> 08:48.226
No, sir.

08:48.228 --> 08:51.196
But found a card on some flowers
sent to tamika's funeral.

08:51.198 --> 08:52.664
Little weird.

08:52.666 --> 08:56.868
"To my pretty boy, r.I.P.,
love always -- easy."

08:56.870 --> 08:58.637
Easy --
Emile's nickname.

08:58.639 --> 09:00.238
Emile? [ Chuckles ]

09:00.240 --> 09:01.640
Well, it certainly is odd

09:01.642 --> 09:03.942
for a dead man to send flowers
to a funeral.

09:03.944 --> 09:07.979
So, obviously, Emile ordered
those flowers before he died.

09:07.981 --> 09:10.715
Maybe that's why
he asked Buddha for money.

09:10.717 --> 09:14.352
And the flowers were sent to
"my pretty boy."

09:14.354 --> 09:15.620
How does that track?

09:15.622 --> 09:18.256
Could Jeremiah
have been Emile's son?

09:18.258 --> 09:19.724
No. No, ma'am.
Too young.

09:19.726 --> 09:22.127
Pretty boy was one of the
nicknames we were looking into

09:22.129 --> 09:24.462
as a possible third man

09:24.464 --> 09:26.665
in the car
during the Reese murders.

09:27.701 --> 09:31.836
So, gang nicknames
are often ironic.

09:31.838 --> 09:34.306
A guy called "tiny"
could be 6'6".

09:34.308 --> 09:37.876
A high-strung, sensitive kid
like Emile is "easy."

09:37.878 --> 09:40.946
Tamika Weaver
was a cute girl.

09:40.948 --> 09:43.248
So they called her
"pretty boy."

09:44.318 --> 09:45.817
Wow.

09:45.819 --> 09:52.123
So the third guy in the car
was not a guy at all.

09:54.194 --> 09:56.528
It was tamika Weaver.

09:56.530 --> 09:57.662
[ Marker cap clicks ]

09:57.664 --> 10:01.166
¶¶

10:05.973 --> 10:07.172
okay, lieutenant.
So, I think I get it.

10:07.174 --> 10:08.907
If tamika Weaver
was pretty boy,

10:08.909 --> 10:10.775
and pretty boy was
the third person in the car...

10:10.777 --> 10:14.479
Ye gods. Each one of
these people has 30 names.

10:14.481 --> 10:15.880
Uh...

10:15.882 --> 10:22.587
Daniel price is trigger
is reverend copkiller.

10:22.589 --> 10:25.056
-Dennis price is...
-Klip.

10:25.058 --> 10:25.890
...klip.

10:25.892 --> 10:27.993
Uh...Uh...
Tamika is...

10:27.995 --> 10:29.694
-Pretty boy.
-...Pretty boy.

10:29.696 --> 10:31.896
And, uh, ah -- Buddha.

10:31.898 --> 10:33.698
Well, he has a different name
altogether.

10:33.700 --> 10:37.068
And not one,
but two hickmans.

10:37.070 --> 10:39.904
Louie, those had better be names
on your guest list.

10:39.906 --> 10:41.272
Well, no.
They're murder suspects.

10:41.274 --> 10:43.575
But, patrice,
w-what are you doing here?

10:43.577 --> 10:45.143
I know
that you're at work,

10:45.145 --> 10:47.879
but I am not planning
this wedding anymore by myself.

10:47.881 --> 10:49.347
Well,
of course you aren't.

10:49.349 --> 10:51.516
I-I'm helping.
I-I'm going to, uh --

10:51.518 --> 10:52.984
Louie,
I said, "let's elope."

10:52.986 --> 10:54.853
I said,
"don't spend lots of money."

10:54.855 --> 10:57.522
I said,
"I am not doing all the work."

10:57.524 --> 10:59.791
No, buzz. You stay.
I'm leaving.

10:59.793 --> 11:02.427
You missed the caterer,
so I can't settle the menu.

11:02.429 --> 11:06.698
Invitations still not ready,
despite what you promised me.

11:06.700 --> 11:10.001
And the guest list --
not filled out.

11:10.003 --> 11:13.538
[ Sighs ]
Louie, honey, look.

11:13.540 --> 11:15.273
We have our license.

11:15.275 --> 11:16.875
Baby, we can just
go across the street

11:16.877 --> 11:18.243
tomorrow during lunch
and --

11:18.245 --> 11:20.712
I am not getting married
during my lunch hour.

11:20.714 --> 11:23.014
Now, look.
The second this case is over,

11:23.016 --> 11:25.350
I will
take care of everything,

11:25.352 --> 11:31.556
and I will make it so beautiful,
like you.

11:31.558 --> 11:35.427
Fill out all of this stuff
and get it back to me tomorrow,

11:35.429 --> 11:37.395
or we do things my way.

11:37.397 --> 11:39.964
Oh, uh, hi, patrice.

11:39.966 --> 11:42.000
Lieutenant,
if you have a minute, um...

11:42.002 --> 11:43.568
He needs to talk to you.

11:43.570 --> 11:44.602
You just hold on.
I was --

11:44.604 --> 11:46.271
Louie, tomorrow.

11:46.273 --> 11:47.439
Tomorrow.

11:47.441 --> 11:48.440
-Bye, buzz.
-Bye.

11:48.442 --> 11:49.674
-Bye, boys.
-Bye.

11:49.676 --> 11:50.842
-Excuse me.
-Bye, patrice.

11:50.844 --> 11:52.177
I'm sorry.
I didn't mean to --

11:52.179 --> 11:54.179
-I didn't mean to interrupt you.
-It's fine.

11:54.181 --> 11:57.716
You probably just ruined
my whole wedding, but so what?

11:57.718 --> 11:58.783
How can I help you?

11:58.785 --> 12:00.719
-Um...
-How?

12:00.721 --> 12:04.823
I...I talked to
m-my other mother

12:04.825 --> 12:06.357
at county last night.

12:06.359 --> 12:08.693
Sharon Beck
won't help you guys

12:08.695 --> 12:10.929
because
her freaky boyfriend, Gary,

12:10.931 --> 12:13.098
said if she did,
he'd kill rusty.

12:13.100 --> 12:14.599
-What?
-O-okay. Okay.

12:14.601 --> 12:17.368
But Gary would never follow
through on a threat like that.

12:17.370 --> 12:19.804
Now we're gonna get this
straightened out right now.

12:19.806 --> 12:23.074
Buzz, I want Sharon Beck brought
over from county immediately.

12:23.076 --> 12:25.443
Thank you, Gus.
Thank you.

12:25.445 --> 12:27.245
Tao: She might have been
Emile's girlfriend,

12:27.247 --> 12:29.948
but tamika was in high school,
just 15.

12:29.950 --> 12:31.850
Found a yearbook picture
of her.

12:31.852 --> 12:34.586
I can see why
they called her pretty boy.

12:34.588 --> 12:35.754
Oh, 15?

12:35.756 --> 12:37.756
Flynn:
Hmm. Underage.

12:37.758 --> 12:40.191
Another reason
why 20-year-old Emile

12:40.193 --> 12:42.260
might have wanted to
keep her out of this.

12:42.262 --> 12:44.295
If tamika was
the third person in the car,

12:44.297 --> 12:46.564
maybe she was also there
when they dumped off the gun.

12:46.566 --> 12:47.966
Let's say she was.

12:47.968 --> 12:50.468
Now, jump ahead
to when reverend copkiller

12:50.470 --> 12:54.205
paid $10,000 bond
to get jon Barnes out of jail.

12:54.207 --> 12:56.708
That is the value of the cash

12:56.710 --> 12:59.611
and the heroin we found
in tamika's car.

12:59.613 --> 13:01.412
Tamika knew who ended up
with the uzi

13:01.414 --> 13:04.115
-and was blackmailing them?
-And got killed in the process.

13:04.117 --> 13:06.451
Yes, that could be a version
of how we ended up here.

13:06.453 --> 13:09.287
Of the three people in the car
when Reese was murdered,

