Does she sound
for real to you?

26:32.491 --> 26:35.326
She does,
but you are right.

26:35.328 --> 26:38.462
It is very hard to know when
your mother's telling the truth.

26:38.464 --> 26:40.965
I guess we'll find out
soon enough.

26:46.806 --> 26:48.372
It only took
an hour and a half

26:48.374 --> 26:50.674
for narco analysis on
the heroin from the motel room.

26:50.676 --> 26:52.076
An exact match to the heroin

26:52.078 --> 26:54.211
jon Barnes was arrested with
two months ago.

26:54.213 --> 26:56.180
I spoke with the officer that
made that arrest, incidentally.

26:56.182 --> 26:58.716
Want to guess
who Barnes had as a lawyer?

26:58.718 --> 27:00.751
-Peter Goldman.
-The one and only.

27:00.753 --> 27:02.820
Goldman also showed up
for six other dealers.

27:02.822 --> 27:04.254
Steph, if you could,
find out

27:04.256 --> 27:06.557
who called Goldman
on those occasions.

27:06.559 --> 27:08.325
Tao:
Here's a problem, though.

27:08.327 --> 27:09.727
The dope from the motel

27:09.729 --> 27:11.662
was cut with baby laxative,
not cornstarch.

27:11.664 --> 27:14.798
So it's not a match with the
heroin found in tamika's car.

27:14.800 --> 27:16.800
Hold on. Now we're talking about
two kinds of heroin?

27:16.802 --> 27:18.802
Tamika's doesn't
link back to the church?

27:18.804 --> 27:20.270
Provenza:
Uh, all right.

27:20.272 --> 27:22.039
Let's not get sidetracked by

27:22.041 --> 27:25.109
all these irrelevant details
about who got high on what.

27:25.111 --> 27:30.214
We have a shootout, so let's
arrest Dennis, a.K.A. Klip,

27:30.216 --> 27:32.650
for the attempted murder
of jon Barnes,

27:32.652 --> 27:34.985
let hobbs and Goldman
deal the guy

27:34.987 --> 27:38.122
into confessing to
all the rest of these murders.

27:38.124 --> 27:41.792
Sorry. Legally, you're looking
at a mutual combat situation.

27:41.794 --> 27:45.262
But Sykes said that it sounded
like Dennis shot first.

27:45.264 --> 27:47.631
Doesn't mean he drew first,
lieutenant.

27:47.633 --> 27:49.066
Goldman will insist

27:49.068 --> 27:50.734
Dennis was defending himself
against Barnes,

27:50.736 --> 27:53.637
-and I can't prove otherwise.
-Maybe there's another angle.

27:53.639 --> 27:55.506
Yeah, more angles --
just what we need.

27:55.508 --> 27:57.107
This one asks us to believe

27:57.109 --> 28:00.444
someone we know to have been
untrustworthy in the past,

28:00.446 --> 28:02.079
but it's worth a shot.

28:02.081 --> 28:05.015
Julio, if you would inform
reverend price that we've had

28:05.017 --> 28:07.418
a break in the case
that requires his attention.

28:07.420 --> 28:08.619
Yes, ma'am.

28:08.621 --> 28:10.220
Goldman will be here
immediately.

28:10.222 --> 28:11.121
I'm counting on it.

28:11.123 --> 28:12.990
In the meantime,
no mention

28:12.992 --> 28:14.625
of Buddha's
statement of facts.

28:14.627 --> 28:16.994
Then what will
we be holding klip on?

28:19.432 --> 28:22.866
The heroin was in the hotel room
when he got there.

28:22.868 --> 28:25.436
Your client is a drug dealer
and now, a murderer.

28:25.438 --> 28:28.472
He is a soldier
in a faith-based community

28:28.474 --> 28:29.973
that's fighting
for its life.

28:29.975 --> 28:33.043
A soldier? That explains
the uzi we found in his church

28:33.045 --> 28:34.878
<i> linked to</i>
<i> at least five murders.</i>

28:34.880 --> 28:37.214
<i> Reese, d.D.A. Gray,</i>
<i> Eric Dunn,</i>

28:37.216 --> 28:39.950
<i> tamika Weaver,</i>
<i> and her son, Jeremiah Barnes.</i>

28:39.952 --> 28:41.318
<i> Is this the same gun</i>
<i> you tried to</i>

28:41.320 --> 28:43.587
<i> pin on his brother</i>
<i> three days ago?</i>

28:43.589 --> 28:46.156
You've been sitting on that gun
for years, haven't you, klip?

28:46.158 --> 28:48.192
-I have not.
-Don't talk.

28:48.194 --> 28:50.294
-Already told you it ain't klip.
-Don't talk.

28:50.296 --> 28:52.596
Was it tamika who told you
where the uzi was

28:52.598 --> 28:54.164
that night you chopped the car

28:54.166 --> 28:57.301
your brother and Emile drove
away from the flower shop?

28:57.303 --> 28:58.836
Did you use that gun
to kill her?

28:58.838 --> 29:00.370
Why would I shoot
that innocent girl?

29:00.372 --> 29:02.773
I said not to talk.

29:02.775 --> 29:05.042
Now,
you can sit here forever

29:05.044 --> 29:07.644
trying to spin straw
into overtime,

29:07.646 --> 29:10.481
but my client
had a religious conversion

29:10.483 --> 29:12.382
that altered his life.

29:12.384 --> 29:14.118
<i> Look, I get it.</i>

29:14.120 --> 29:15.652
[ Cellphone vibrates ]
<i> It must be very frustrating</i>

29:15.654 --> 29:18.522
<i> to have mishandled a case</i>
<i> this badly.</i>
Hello?

29:18.524 --> 29:21.725
<i> It is at times like these cops</i>
<i> start forcing investigation...</i>

29:21.727 --> 29:23.060
Captain, that was julio.

29:23.062 --> 29:24.962
He's on his way up
with reverend price.

29:24.964 --> 29:26.663
<i> ...but my client...</i>

29:26.665 --> 29:28.365
-Mike, do you have the --
-yes.

29:28.367 --> 29:31.235
Julio has the rest, including
the, uh, charges for the motel.

29:31.237 --> 29:33.504
Lieutenant,
would you care to join me?

29:33.506 --> 29:35.005
<i> ...wanted by the police.</i>

29:35.007 --> 29:37.474
Flynn:<i> He went there with a gun.</i>
<i> He shot first.</i>

29:37.476 --> 29:40.878
As I understand it, you arrested
my client for protecting himself

29:40.880 --> 29:44.148
from a man
you told me yesterday

29:44.150 --> 29:47.217
had shot and killed
three innocent teenagers.

29:47.219 --> 29:49.386
Now, my client's
supposed to approach

29:49.388 --> 29:50.788
<i> a man like that unarmed?</i>

29:50.790 --> 29:53.323
Well, he could have
called the police.

29:53.325 --> 29:55.526
Reverend price.

29:55.528 --> 29:57.427
-Thank you for coming.
-Peace and out, captain.

29:57.429 --> 29:58.796
That's all
you're getting from me

29:58.798 --> 29:59.997
until I hear back
from my lawyer.

29:59.999 --> 30:01.398
He doesn't know, ma'am.

30:01.400 --> 30:02.332
Know what?

30:02.334 --> 30:04.535
Uh, well,
we'll get to that.

30:04.537 --> 30:08.372
Why don't you join us in
the conference room over here?

30:08.374 --> 30:12.743
Uh, you're lawyer will
be with us in a minute.

30:12.745 --> 30:14.244
You called Peter, too?

30:14.246 --> 30:15.979
We didn't need to,
reverend.

30:15.981 --> 30:18.448
Goldman:
The way I see it, at worst,

30:18.450 --> 30:21.218
you've got Dennis on
a misdemeanor weapons charge

30:21.220 --> 30:23.487
for firing his gun
within city limits.

30:23.489 --> 30:26.490
And for that...

30:26.492 --> 30:28.759
I will gladly go downstairs

30:28.761 --> 30:33.230
and pay the $100 fine myself
to end this discussion.

30:33.232 --> 30:36.533
You will not question my client
while I'm gone.

30:36.535 --> 30:39.002
Dennis, stay calm.

30:39.004 --> 30:40.604
Sure thing.

30:40.606 --> 30:42.739
I'll be back shortly.

30:42.741 --> 30:46.043
¶¶

30:55.588 --> 30:57.487
what is this?
Wha--

30:57.489 --> 30:59.223
you guys wipe your feet

30:59.225 --> 31:01.458
on the constitution
every chance you get.

31:01.460 --> 31:03.060
No,
we were only waiting on --

31:03.062 --> 31:05.062
I'm, frankly, disappointed
in you, captain.

31:05.064 --> 31:06.663
We only now just sat down.

31:06.665 --> 31:09.800
You know better than to question
him without his lawyer present.

31:09.802 --> 31:11.935
We haven't asked him
any questions.

31:11.937 --> 31:13.704
We were just going to
give him a...

31:13.706 --> 31:15.672
Courtesy briefing
on our progress.

31:15.674 --> 31:18.242
Because you're so famous
for your courtesy, lieutenant?

31:18.244 --> 31:21.011
No, it's a trick,
and we're leaving.

31:21.013 --> 31:23.113
-Daniel, let's go.
-I am so sorry, reverend.

31:23.115 --> 31:25.315
I had hoped to be able
to explain to you

31:25.317 --> 31:27.517
why we arrested
your brother today,

31:27.519 --> 31:30.187
but you can hear about it
on the news later.

31:30.189 --> 31:32.055
-What are you talking about?
-It's ridiculous.

31:32.057 --> 31:33.724
I'll tell you outside.
Let's go.

31:33.726 --> 31:36.560
Your brother was in a shootout
with one of your parishioners,

31:36.562 --> 31:40.163
Mr. jon Barnes,
who you bailed out of jail.

31:40.165 --> 31:42.666
What? Peter?
You know about this?

31:42.668 --> 31:45.903
Oh, reverend, that is why
Mr. Goldman is here.

31:45.905 --> 31:48.071
Dennis called me.

31:48.073 --> 31:50.574
He was worried
that you would be angry.

31:50.576 --> 31:53.377
But it was all a trick to
distract me

31:53.379 --> 31:55.512
so they could take advantage
of you like this.

31:55.514 --> 31:57.214
Please, come with me.

31:57.216 --> 32:00.384
And make sure that Mr. Goldman
doesn't forget the details

32:00.386 --> 32:02.252
of how your brother
has been

32:02.254 --> 32:04.488
running heroin
through your church.

32:04.490 --> 32:05.856
Shame on, detective.

32:05.858 --> 32:07.524
My brother's been
on the straight for years

32:07.526 --> 32:10.093
-thanks to the blood of Christ.
-No, thanks to Mr. Goldman,

32:10.095 --> 32:12.596
who's managed to
keep you in the dark.

32:12.598 --> 32:15.966
We found this heroin
in the same motel room

32:15.968 --> 32:17.634
where your brother stashed
jon Barnes.

32:17.636 --> 32:19.202
We just traced back
the credit card

32:19.204 --> 32:21.138
paying for the room
to Dennis price.

32:21.140 --> 32:24.775
And he has several other
motel rooms he started using

32:24.777 --> 32:26.310
right before
we searched your church.

32:26.312 --> 32:27.911
They're
playing a game with you.

32:27.913 --> 32:29.579
I want to listen, Peter.
Let him finish.

32:29.581 --> 32:31.481
-What else?
-Are you really not aware

32:31.483 --> 32:34.418
that Mr. Goldman is
working for your brother?

32:34.420 --> 32:37.220
Of course
he's working for my brother.

32:37.222 --> 32:39.623
Peter works for our church,
our community.

32:39.625 --> 32:41.158
-And my brother obviously --
-seven arrests

32:41.160 --> 32:42.759
in your neighborhood
in the last six months,

32:42.761 --> 32:45.395
all of them dealers supposedly
working for your brother

32:45.397 --> 32:47.564
and all of them represented
by Peter Goldman.

32:47.566 --> 32:49.132
Daniel, I promise,

32:49.134 --> 32:51.535
I can explain
everything they're lying about.

32:51.537 --> 32:53.704
Then, Peter, please tell
the reverend that 40 minutes

32:53.706 --> 32:57.107
after jon Barnes was arrested
for dealing heroin,

32:57.109 --> 33:00.310
your brother, Dennis,
called your cellphone.

33:00.312 --> 33:01.712
Sanchez:
And you showed up for jon Barnes

33:01.714 --> 33:03.480
and you represented him
at his arraignment.

33:03.482 --> 33:06.316
That's your proof that
I'm involved in the drug trade?

33:06.318 --> 33:09.219
-Really?
-No, not by itself. No.

33:09.221 --> 33:11.388
But we went back
and cross-checked

33:11.390 --> 33:13.457
the other six arrests
we mentioned,

33:13.459 --> 33:18.195
and, as you can see, your
brother called Mr. Goldman here

33:18.197 --> 33:21.598
within the hour
of each booking.

33:24.136 --> 33:26.470
There's your proof, Peter.

33:29.975 --> 33:31.241
Is this true?

33:31.243 --> 33:33.276
These people
will say anything --

33:33.278 --> 33:34.778
was my brother calling you

33:34.780 --> 33:37.247
to defend the very people
leeching off our community?!

33:37.249 --> 33:39.783
Daniel, if you'll just
follow me outside,

33:39.785 --> 33:41.151
I can explain everything.

33:41.153 --> 33:43.520
Your steps are not
the ones I follow!

33:43.522 --> 33:45.455
Is Dennis...

33:45.457 --> 33:47.657
Are you being paid
by my brother?

33:55.134 --> 33:57.634
There's your answer,
reverend.

34:01.407 --> 34:04.608
You and I are finished, Peter,
understand?

34:04.610 --> 34:07.744
And for what you've done,
may God forgive you.

34:07.746 --> 34:09.780
What I did, Daniel,

34:09.782 --> 34:13.850
was to protect your work.

34:13.852 --> 34:15.519
I'll go.

34:15.521 --> 34:17.421
But I urge you
to stay silent.

34:17.423 --> 34:21.758
These people mean to
do you and your community harm.

34:21.760 --> 34:26.396
And without me beside you,
they may well succeed.

34:29.368 --> 34:31.268
Mr. price,
we have more evidence

34:31.270 --> 34:34.104
about your brother's drug
business than Peter knows.

34:36.141 --> 34:38.442
Provenza:
That is a statement of facts

34:38.444 --> 34:42.913
from Mr. Greg mann,
a.K.A. Buddha.

34:42.915 --> 34:47.884
Now, Mr. Buddha is going into
the Witness Protection program.

34:47.886 --> 34:50.187
In exchange,
he will explain

34:50.189 --> 34:56.693
how your brother used your
church for drug trafficking.

35:00.165 --> 35:02.199
[ Sighs ]

35:02.201 --> 35:05.502
I don't trust Peter...

35:05.504 --> 35:07.370
But I don't trust you,
either.

35:08.273 --> 35:10.173
How can I be sure
all of this is true?

35:10.175 --> 35:12.375
There's only one way,
reverend.

35:12.377 --> 35:14.010
What would that be?

35:14.012 --> 35:19.082
We need you to have
a heart-to-heart conversation

35:19.084 --> 35:20.417
with your brother.

35:31.330 --> 35:33.096
<i> In the middle of what</i>
<i> community leaders called</i>

35:33.098 --> 35:35.565
<i> a heated racially charged</i>
<i> gang war, the l.A.P.D. Remains</i>

35:35.567 --> 35:37.234
<i> tight-lipped</i>
<i> about their progress.</i>

35:37.236 --> 35:39.002
<i> Even though</i>
<i> crime suppression units</i>

35:39.004 --> 35:41.404
<i> can be found throughout the</i>
<i> Adams-normandie neighborhood,</i>

35:41.406 --> 35:42.806
<i> residents say they still...</i>

35:42.808 --> 35:45.108
Mr. Sanchez?

35:45.110 --> 35:46.610
Dr. foster's ready for you.

35:46.612 --> 35:49.713
<i> ...extremely windy and cold,</i>
<i> unseasonably so.</i>

35:49.715 --> 35:53.183
<i> It appears as if</i>
<i> the, uh, weather system</i>

35:53.185 --> 35:54.885
<i> is gonna be moving through</i>
<i> the area</i>

35:54.887 --> 35:56.953
<i> throughout the next</i>
<i> several days.</i>

35:56.955 --> 35:58.688
<i>It's something that we'll be...</i>

36:04.096 --> 36:05.529
[ Door opens ]

36:05.531 --> 36:08.465
Mr. Sanchez.

36:08.467 --> 36:10.133
It's been a long time.

36:10.135 --> 36:13.170
Over 15 years, yeah.

36:13.172 --> 36:15.438
Your office hasn't changed much,
sir.

36:15.440 --> 36:18.375
No.
Well, I have a laptop now

36:18.377 --> 36:20.710
and my new patients
are fully digitized.

36:20.712 --> 36:23.280
But I have your wife's records
here.

36:23.282 --> 36:24.814
What would you
like to know?

36:24.816 --> 36:29.686
I'm here to ask a-about...

36:29.688 --> 36:32.055
Maria's...

36:32.057 --> 36:34.491
About how she died,
sir.

36:36.261 --> 36:38.995
Mr. Sanchez,
your wife passed away

36:38.997 --> 36:41.531
from concussive injuries
sustained in a car accident.

36:41.533 --> 36:43.333
During a seizure,
a seizure that happened

36:43.335 --> 36:45.769
because you took her
off her meds.

36:45.771 --> 36:47.671
Why did you do that?

36:47.673 --> 36:50.640
Why did you take Maria
off her medication?

36:50.642 --> 36:54.411
The short answer is
I didn't.

36:54.413 --> 36:56.546
In fact,
because the dose was so mild,

36:56.548 --> 36:59.182
I suggested Maria keep on it
for another year.

36:59.184 --> 37:01.518
No. No, no.
No, wait. Wait.

37:01.520 --> 37:05.822
Maria said you told her
she could go off her meds.

37:05.824 --> 37:07.724
No. I didn't.

37:07.726 --> 37:10.327
In fact,
I had Maria sign a form

37:10.329 --> 37:13.296
stating that
by discontinuing dilantin,

37:13.298 --> 37:16.733
she was acting against
the advice of a doctor

37:16.735 --> 37:21.238
and understood
the potential consequences.

37:21.240 --> 37:23.340
And I also urged Maria

37:23.342 --> 37:26.042
to discuss her decision
with her family.

37:26.044 --> 37:28.478
She never...

37:28.480 --> 37:30.647
Talked to me about this.

37:30.649 --> 37:34.718
Never would I have agreed
to this in a million years.

37:35.921 --> 37:38.121
Are you sure
it would have made a difference?

37:38.123 --> 37:39.456
From what I recall,

37:39.458 --> 37:41.858
when your wife
felt strongly about something,

37:41.860 --> 37:45.295
she did not shy away
from confrontation.

37:45.297 --> 37:47.998
No. No.

37:49.868 --> 37:51.968
She mostly got her way.

37:51.970 --> 37:57.807
She didn't ever just out-and-out
lie to me, sir.

37:57.809 --> 38:02.245
Maybe Maria found a way
to phrase her decision

38:02.247 --> 38:05.181
so it sounded less drastic
than it was.

38:05.183 --> 38:07.851
¶¶

38:07.853 --> 38:10.020
Flynn: We should be able to
hear something very soon.

38:10.022 --> 38:11.488
The wire's active.

38:11.490 --> 38:13.523
Patrollers are driving
Dennis price to the church

38:13.525 --> 38:16.059
and his brother is waiting
for him in his office.

38:16.061 --> 38:17.394
Confession imminent.

38:17.396 --> 38:18.928
I don't know about that.

38:18.930 --> 38:19.929
Why so pessimistic?

38:19.931 --> 38:22.399
The gunfight at the motel
yesterday

38:22.401 --> 38:25.835
just doesn't fit the profile
of our killer,

38:25.837 --> 38:30.040
and mark hickman was following
Rachel gray 12 years ago.

38:30.042 --> 38:31.308
Checking out her security.

38:31.310 --> 38:34.511
Oh, no.
He was lying about that.

38:34.513 --> 38:38.281
But was he also
lying in wait?

38:38.283 --> 38:41.318
Well...

38:41.320 --> 38:43.320
I am.

38:44.823 --> 38:47.290
For a second
to be alone with you.

38:47.292 --> 38:50.593
¶¶

38:53.098 --> 38:55.265
so, uh, tell me.

38:55.267 --> 38:58.835
Did you get a chance to
reschedule your NFL interview?

38:58.837 --> 39:00.704
No. Not yet.

39:00.706 --> 39:01.738
Oh.

39:01.740 --> 39:04.274
So, you're passing
on the security job?

39:04.276 --> 39:06.309
-Or what?
-Andy, I don't know.

39:06.311 --> 39:08.111
I don't know.

39:08.113 --> 39:10.613
All that travel means that we
will see each other even less.

39:10.615 --> 39:14.884
And rusty is still
so very vulnerable and...

39:14.886 --> 39:16.920
And?

39:16.922 --> 39:19.389
And I spent
my entire career

39:19.391 --> 39:22.692
ridding the l.A.P.D.
Of officers

39:22.694 --> 39:25.562
like mark hickman
and their influence.

39:25.564 --> 39:29.632
And I'm pretty sure
that Amy is talking with him.

39:29.634 --> 39:31.935
Yeah, yeah.
I know how it looks.

39:31.937 --> 39:35.772
But remember, Taylor told you
to leave hickman out of it.

39:35.774 --> 39:37.974
He never told us
to avoid him,

39:37.976 --> 39:39.743
and neither did you,
for that matter.

39:39.745 --> 39:42.946
Slicing things pretty thin.

39:42.948 --> 39:45.348
Information was withheld.

39:45.350 --> 39:46.950
Was it?

39:46.952 --> 39:50.553
Or did we just hear some
theories about these murders

39:50.555 --> 39:52.956
without knowing
whose they were?

39:52.958 --> 39:54.758
Go ahead.
-Hmm?

39:54.760 --> 39:56.426
Ask Amy.

39:56.428 --> 39:58.294
She's not gonna
lie to your face.

39:58.296 --> 40:00.029
I know that.

40:00.932 --> 40:04.000
Provenza: Why can't I tell
what's going on?

40:04.002 --> 40:06.035
And -- and where did
the reverend copkiller go?

40:06.037 --> 40:09.539
And why did the button cam
suddenly go so dark?

40:09.541 --> 40:11.674
I think he's kneeling
by his desk.

40:11.676 --> 40:14.377
It's a good sign. Maybe praying
for strength to help us.

40:14.379 --> 40:15.678
